function (uint256,address,uint256,bytes memory) payable external returns (bytes memory)

params.daoAddress: The address of a DAO participant.

params.index: The index of the an address.

params.universalProfileAddress: The address of a Universal Profile.

params.name: Name of the DAO.
params.participationRate: The percentage of pro and against votes compared to abstain votes needed for a proposal to pass.
params.quorum: The percentage of pro votes from the sum of pro and against votes needed for a proposal to pass.
params.votingDelay: Time required to pass before a proposal goes to the voting phase.
params.votingPeriod: Time allowed for voting on a proposal.

params.datas: The calldata that will be executed if the proposall passes.
params.targets: The addresses of the smart contracts that might have calldata executed.
params.title: Title of the proposal.

params.proposalSignature: The abi.encode bytes32 signature of a proposal.
The bytes10 signature of a proposal.

params.universalProfileAddress: The address of a Universal Profile.

params.proposalSignature: The abi.encode bytes32 signature of a proposal.
params.voteIndex: a number 0 <= `voteIndex` <= 1. Index 0 are the against votes.  Index 1 are the pro votes.

_getDaoAddressByIndex(uint256).notice: Get an address of a DAO perticipant by index.

_getDaoAddressesArrayLength().notice: Get the length of the array of the addresses that are participants of the DAO.

_getDaoDescription().notice: Get the description of the DAO.

_getDaoName().notice: Get the name of the DAO.

_getDaoParticipationRate().notice: Get the participation rate of the DAO.

_getDaoQuorum().notice: Get the quorum of the DAO.

_getDaoVotingDelay().notice: Get the voting delay of the DAO.

_getDaoVotingPeriod().notice: Get the voting period of the DAO.

_getDelegateeOfTheDelegator(address).notice: Get the delgatee of the delegator.

_getDelegatorByIndex(address,uint256).notice: Get the delegator of the delagtee by index.

_getDelegatorsArrayLength(address).notice: Get the length of the array of addresses that delegated the votes to a delegatee.

_getPermissionsByIndex(uint8).notice: Get the the bytes32 permission from the permissions array.

_getTargetsAndDatas(bytes10).notice: Get the targets and datas for execution of a proposal.

_getVotedStatus(address,bytes10).notice: Get voted status of a Universal Profile for a proposal.

addPermission(address,uint8).notice: Add permission to an address by index. Index 0 sets the VOTE permission. Index 1 sets the PROPOSE permission. Index 2 sets the SEND_DELEGATE permission. Index 3 sets the RECIEVE_DELEGATE permission. Index 4 sets the MASTER permission.

constructor.notice: Initialization of the Universal Profile Account as a DAO Account; This smart contract will be given all controller permissions. Here is where all the tools needed for a functioning DAO are initialized.

createProposal(string,string,address[],b.notice: Create a proposal. The proposal signature is encoded to a bytes10 variable. Which is later used compined with an attribute key for getting the attribute value.

delegate(address).notice: Delegate your vote to another participant of the DAO

endProposal(bytes10).notice: End proposal and execute the calldata. Encode the proposal info, timestamps and results and save them to the Universal Profile of the DAO.

putProposalToVote(bytes10).notice: Move the proposal to the voting phase. Save the current timestamp.

removePermission(address,uint8).notice: Remove the permission of an Unversal Profile by index. Index 0 unsets the VOTE permission. Index 1 unsets the PROPOSE permission. Index 2 unsets the SEND_DELEGATE permission. Index 3 unsets the RECIEVE_DELEGATE permission. Index 4 unsets the MASTER permission.

userdoc.notice: This smart contract is responsible for connecting all the necessary tools for a DAO based on Universal Profiles (LSP0ERC725Account)
